<capabilities>
<p>The Kublai inherits the Qasar's fundamental strengths: an eighty-ton airframe driven by a 400-rated XL engine that delivers thrust performance rivaling craft thirty tons lighter, and twenty-six tons of pod space allowing substantial weapon configurations. Twenty double heat sinks integrated into the base chassis provide adequate thermal management for most loadouts. The critical improvement lies in the Naketsu Nagareboshi laser reflective armor system, which dramatically improves survivability against the energy-heavy armaments common to both Clan and Inner Sphere aerospace forces. Where the original Qasar's thin conventional armor invited destruction, the Kublai can weather laser and PPC fire that would cripple its predecessor.</p>
</capabilities>

<overview>
<p>The Kublai represents the Draconis Combine's pragmatic approach to captured enemy assets. Following the destruction of Clan Nova Cat in 3142, Combine forces found themselves in possession of Delta Refit Center on Irece and its production lines for the Qasar heavy OmniFighter. Rather than discard a proven airframe, Combine engineers addressed the design's most critical flaw through application of Naketsu Nagareboshi laser reflective armor plating. The resulting fighter was designated the Kublaiâ€”an ironic name evoking Mongol conquest, now turned to serve the Dragon. While retaining the exceptional thrust and pod capacity that made the Qasar formidable, the Kublai transforms a defensive liability into a tactical advantage against energy-weapon-heavy opponents. Production continues at Delta Refit Center, with the Kublai entering regular service with Draconis Combine Mustered Soldiery aerospace formations.</p>
</overview>

<deployment>
<p>This configuration combines advanced energy weapons with missile systems for versatile engagement options. Twin Improved Heavy Large Lasers in the nose deliver concentrated damage at medium range, while an MRM 30 launcher guided by an Apollo Fire Control System provides accurate supplementary firepower. An ECM Suite enhances survivability against guided weapons. The combination of precision energy weapons and volume missile fire makes this variant effective against both aerospace and ground targets.</p>
</deployment>

<history>
<p>The Kublai's history begins with the end of Clan Nova Cat. When the Nova Cats revolted against the Draconis Combine in 3141, their resurrected Qasar OmniFighters initially dominated the aerospace battlespace. Combine pilots in aging Slayers and Rievers found themselves outmatched by the heavy Clan fighters. Only through disciplined teamwork and tactical adaptation did Combine squadrons learn to counter the Qasar's advantages, exploiting its thin armor and limited fuel capacity through coordinated attacks rather than individual engagements.</p>
</history>

